                    </div>
                </details>

                <details class="border border-slate-200 rounded-lg mb-3 not-prose">
                    <summary class="p-4 font-bold cursor-pointer hover:bg-slate-50">
                        Do I have to stay in the nominating province forever?
                    </summary>
                    <div class="p-4 pt-0 text-slate-600">
                        No. The Canadian Charter of Rights and Freedoms guarantees mobility rights to all
                        permanent residents. However, you must have a genuine intention to live in the
                        province when you apply. Moving immediately after landing may raise concerns for
                        future applications (like citizenship) and could affect others applying through
                        that province.
                    </div>
                </details>

                <details class="border border-slate-200 rounded-lg mb-3 not-prose">
                    <summary class="p-4 font-bold cursor-pointer hover:bg-slate-50">
                        What happens if my PNP application is refused?
                    </summary>
                    <div class="p-4 pt-0 text-slate-600">
